\cb3 Comments for the Authors\cb1 \
\cb3 I read the "ideas and perspectives" piece by Kharouba & Wolkovitch with great interest, and very much enjoyed it. The work presents a well-argued critique of the current state-of-the-art in research into the food web effects of phenological change. Important take home messages are that rigorous hypothesis testing, mechanistic understanding, and a sound knowledge of historical baselines are vital to progress in the field. While I recognise that, in reality, it will be extremely challenging to meet all of these demands, I feel that the case is well argued. Uncharacteristically, I have no comments and would be happy to see this published as is. I commend the authors on an excellent piece of work!\cb1 \
